headline: Quest (NYSE:DGX) Posts Better-Than-Expected Sales In Q3
summary: Healthcare diagnostics company Quest Diagnostics (NYSE:DGX) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 13.2% year on year to $2.82 billion. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $10.98 billion at the midpoint came in 1% above analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.60 per share was 3.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
